reviewText: Came on time and the discs work fine

For years I had a grudge against Tom Cruise, though I can't remember why. But I decided to give him another try and bought this album of the MI movies. I remember the first MI movie, and I liked it. But I was really impressed with the whole four-movie series. As far as action movies though, these are quite exceptional. Whether you buy them separately or altogether, I highly recommend these.
I love the Mission Impossible franchise! Can't get enough of it. May be Tom would be willing to get it another go? Let's hope!
I bought this set twice and neither one of them worked. poor quality control! I must say that the return process was very easy and fast.
received as expected in good condition.
I was a bit concerned that I wouldn't have room on the shelf for 4 dvds so was pleasantly surprised that it came in one box.  It's exactly what I wanted and the deliver was great.
Great if your a MI fan

I'm picking up the films one by one, not this way, for the simple reason that "quadrilogy" is a made-up word (you can't mix Latin and Greek). It's a tetralogy, or to be on safer ground, anthology.

A Christmas Gift for my Dad. Only complaint, the packaging, not very good. I shook the box & I could hear 2 of the blue rays popped out of the
insert & were bouncing around. Also, outer box sleeve was torn. Come on guys!
Since I've seen all of these movies, ordering this bundle was great
